sec.p:
The charged particles of polymer have great influence on jet formation. When the conductivity of the solution is too low, there will be beads and it is difficult to form uniform nanofibers. However, high conductivity may lead to bending whiplash and uneven diameter or formation of ribbon fibers [134]. The diameter of nanofibers decreases with the increase in the conductivity [113, 135]. Some researchers also found the conductivity has negligible effect on the fiber diameter [126]. It has been found that theoretically the jet radius is inversely proportional to the cube root of the solution conductivity [51]:1r0=4εQkπσρ3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
